In 1.2.0-dev, mongoc_topology_select is responsible for selecting a server from your deployment for an operation. In pooled clients, if mongoc_topology_select doesn't know of a suitable server, it uses a condition variable to wait up to serverSelectionTimeoutMS for the monitor thread to discover one.

To use pthread_cond_wait, the driver begins by calculating the current time in milliseconds since the epoch:
{code}
   struct timeval tv;
   int64_t msec;

   bson_gettimeofday (&tv);
   msec = (tv.tv_sec * 1000) + (tv.tv_usec / 1000) + timeout_msec;
{code}
This works on platforms where tv_sec is a 64-bit int, but on Solaris it's 32 bits and overflows. (These days, representing tv_sec requires 31 bits, so multiplying it by 1000 overflows.)

The driver constructs a negative timespec from this calculation and passes it to pthread_cond_wait, which returns EINVAL and mongoc_topology_select quits.

The following error recently popped up in the [PHPC builds|https://travis-ci.org/10gen-labs/mongo-php-driver-prototype/jobs/71836870#L1066] after [~bjori] added {{-Werror}} to our build flags ([here|https://github.com/10gen-labs/mongo-php-driver-prototype/commit/8087ab6d97970e1e9162ce6798e244127dc12bbf]):

{quote}
home/travis/build/10gen-labs/mongo-php-driver-prototype/src/libmongoc/src/mongoc/mongoc-matcher-op.c:165:4: error: comparison of unsigned expression >= 0 is always true \[-Werror=type-limits\]
{quote}

I traced this back to [this commit|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/commit/a07a0a12eba75b16371a2c060309c4320ff2c1de#diff-0252e1758ec4cd4f113669b69b800d65L84].

While we could suppress this error with {{\[-Wno-type-limits\]}}, that might hide other errors, too. Some ideas tossed around in [this thread|http://arstechnica.com/civis/viewtopic.php?f=20&t=1130118] include adding an unused negative value to the enum to force a signed type to be used (which seems noisy) or to for a signed cast before the comparison. Alternatively, we can just do without the {{>= MONGOC_MATCHER_OPCODE_EQ}} part of the assertion if we want to rely on the enum being unsigned and {{MONGOC_MATCHER_OPCODE_EQ}} being zero.

